metadata.name: Vorticity #49
metadata.description:
Vorticity is a gpu-accelerated flow field. The particles in the flow field orbit around a set of points that move around over time.

Controls: Click and drag to push particles away. Press the space bar to pause the simulation, and again to resume. While paused, you can press "n" to advance the simulation a single step. Press "r" to restart the simulation (if you change the resolution of the screen after the page loads, you will need to restart to update the resolution).

There are a variety of styles and backgrounds.

Code is based on my open source sprite generator ZzSprite.

Audio is using my open source sound effect system ZzFX.

metadata.name: Liny_Dancers #51
metadata.description:
Liny_Dancers.
I wrote four lines.

The simple shapes reminded me of people are dancing.
I enjoyed it and felt happy again.

I wanted a result quite minimally.
I wanted to cram in all kinds of ideas.
But I decided against it.

The maximum number of dancers would be five dancers.

But the more dancers, It will be Rare.

I feel joy, emotion, and melancholy from the way they dance.

Please enjoy it.
